HOUSE BILL 1587
C7 6lr3639
By: Delegate Patterson
Introduced and read first time: February 15, 2026
Assigned to: Rules and Executive Nominations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Gaming – Electronic Instant Bingo Machines – Operation and Maximum
3 Number of Machines
4 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “slot machine” to repeal a limitation on the
5 number of bingo cards certain handheld devices may allow a user to play at the same
6 time; increasing the number of electronic instant bingo machines that certain
7 entities may operate; providing that an electronic instant bingo machine is not
8 required to print a paper ticket for each instant bingo game played except under
9 certain circumstances; and generally relating to electronic instant bingo machines.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Criminal Law
12 Section 12–301, 12–301.1(e), and 12–308
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Chapter 603 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2012
17 Section 3
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Criminal Law
21 12–301.
22 In this subtitle:
23 (1) “slot machine” means a machine, apparatus, or device that:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
