2 HOUSE BILL 1587
1 (i) operates or can be made to operate by inserting, depositing, or
2 placing with another person money, a token, or another object; and
3 (ii) through the element of chance, the reading of a game of chance,
4 the delivery of a game of chance, or any other outcome unpredictable by the user, awards
5 the user:
6 1. money, a token, or other object that represents or that can
7 be converted into money; or
8 2. the right to receive money, a token, or another object that
9 represents and can be converted into money;
10 (2) “slot machine” includes:
11 (i) a machine, apparatus, or device described in item (1) of this
12 section that also sells, delivers, or awards merchandise, money, or some other tangible
13 thing of value;
14 (ii) a pinball machine or console machine that pays off in
15 merchandise; and
16 (iii) a machine, apparatus, or device described in item (1) of this
17 section, regardless of whether the machine, apparatus, or device delivers a game through
18 the Internet or offers Internet or other services; and
19 (3) “slot machine” does not include a machine, apparatus, or device that:
20 (i) awards the user only free additional games or plays;
21 (ii) awards the user only noncash merchandise or noncash prizes of
22 minimal value;
23 (iii) dispenses paper pull tab tip jar tickets or paper pull tab instant
24 bingo tickets that must be opened manually by the user provided that the machine,
25 apparatus, or device does not:
26 1. read the tickets electronically;
27 2. alert the user to a winning or losing ticket; or
28 3. tabulate a player’s winnings and losses;
29 (iv) 1. is a handheld device that displays only facsimiles of bingo
30 cards that an individual uses to mark and monitor contemporaneously to a live call of bingo
31 numbers called on the premises by an individual where the user is operating the machine;

